// translate-expr.scrml ‚Äî M5-swap Unit A2 ‚Äî the EXPRESSION-CATALOG BRIDGE: the
// native-parser analogue that translates the native PascalCase `Expr` catalog
// into the live lowercase `ExprNode` union the downstream codegen walks.
//
// PILLAR 5b classification (DD ¬ßD1):
//   translateExpr is CALCULATION (pure). It is a recursive tree-walk over the
//   native parser's `Expr` ‚Äî read-only, no cursor, no engine, no lifecycle, no
//   threaded state. Unlike the statement bridge it takes NO id-allocator: the
//   live `ExprNode` union carries NO numeric `id` (the `id` field is the
//   `BaseNode` contract for STATEMENT / MARKUP nodes, not for expression
//   nodes). So the calculation is a pure shape map. The spec's `fn` + struct
//   primitives are sufficient; no missing primitive surfaced.
//
// PURPOSE ‚Äî the expression-catalog bridge:
//   The native parser's `parse-expr.js` emits a PascalCase ESTree-shaped
//   `Expr` ‚Äî the `ast-expr.js` `ExprKind` catalog (40 closed entries: Ident /
//   NumberLit / Binary / Conditional / IsCheck / Call / ...). The live
//   `FileAST` codegen layer dispatches a scrml-specific LOWERCASE `ExprNode`
//   union ‚Äî ident / lit / binary / ternary / member / call / ... (ast.ts:1939,
//   20 kinds). The codegen emitter `emit-expr.ts` walks the lowercase union;
//   `ast-expr.js` produces the PascalCase catalog. The two catalogs DIVERGE
//   structurally ‚Äî kind-rename, fan-out, fan-in. This module is the
//   reconciliation. It is the direct sibling of R1's `translate-stmt` (the
//   statement-catalog bridge); R1 rode expression children through VERBATIM
//   and explicitly deferred this unit. A2 closes that deferral.
//
// TRANSLATION LOCUS (A2 design decision ‚Äî mirrors R1): a native-parser
//   EXIT-SHAPING module, sibling of `collect-hoisted` / `translate-stmt` ‚Äî
//   NOT a mutation of `parse-expr`. `parseExpression` stays pure (still emits
//   the native `Expr`); this module is an OPTIONAL exit shaper the FileAST
//   assembler (Unit C1) invokes ‚Äî and that the statement bridge calls into for
//   every expression CHILD it currently rides through verbatim.
//
// THE NATIVE -> LIVE EXPRESSION-KIND MAP:
//   KIND-RENAME:
//     native Ident         -> live ident
//     native AtCell        -> live ident   (the `@` rides in `name`)
//     native BareVariant   -> live ident   (the `.` rides in `name`)
//     native Tilde         -> live ident   (`name` is the literal "~")
//     native Array         -> live array
//     native Object        -> live object
//     native Unary         -> live unary
//     native Binary        -> live binary
//     native Assignment    -> live assign
//     native Conditional   -> live ternary
//     native Call          -> live call
//     native New           -> live new
//     native Sql           -> live sql-ref          (nodeId -1; C1 re-stamps)
//     native InputStateRef -> live input-state-ref
//     native Match         -> live match-expr
//   FAN-IN:
//     native NumberLit / StringLit / BoolLit / RegexLit / TemplateLit
//                          -> live lit  (litType discriminates)
//     native NotValue      -> live lit { litType: "not" }   (¬ß42 absence)
//     native Logical       -> live binary  (JS `&&`/`||`/`??` are BinaryExpr
//                             `op` values ‚Äî no separate `logical` kind)
//     native Update        -> live unary   (`++`/`--` are UnaryExpr `op`
//                             values; the `prefix` flag carries pre/post)
//     native Arrow / Function -> live lambda  (`fnStyle` discriminates)
//   FAN-OUT:
//     native IsCheck -> live binary, `op` selected by the IsCheckOp:
//       Not -> "is-not" ¬∑ Some/Given -> "is-some" ¬∑ NotNot -> "is-not-not" ¬∑
//       Variant -> "is" (the `x is .V` variant form; `right` is the variant)
//     native Member -> live member (computed:false) / live index (computed:true)
//   PASSTHROUGH-UNWRAP:
//     native Paren -> the inner expression (no live `paren` kind ‚Äî parentheses
//       are a parse-grouping artifact; codegen re-parenthesizes by precedence)
//   ESCAPE-HATCH (no clean live target ‚Äî SURFACED to PA as gaps, not papered
//   over): This / Super / TaggedTemplate / Sequence / Yield / Render /
//     MarkupValue (and Lift / Fail at a genuine expression-child position ‚Äî
//     the common statement-position case is intercepted by translate-stmt).
//     These route to live `escape-hatch` with `nativeKind` set (the S115 /
//     DD #27 `estreeType`->`nativeKind` rename ‚Äî a sub-kind decoration, not a
//     translation surface). emit-expr.ts:emitEscapeHatch's dual-mode path
//     already recognizes native kind strings, so the escape-hatch keeps
//     codegen crash-free + the output correct via the string-rewrite fallback.
//
// SCOPE BOUNDARY (A2, IMPORTANT): A2 translates ONLY what the native parser
//   already PRODUCES. It is INDEPENDENT of the Tier-B parser-feature-gap units
//   (`?` propagate, `!{}` guarded-expr, `~`-decl, `lin`, `fn`/`server`/`pure`
//   modifiers, `type`) ‚Äî those are v0.7 work and the native parser has no
//   production for them yet. A2 adds NO parser productions and invents NO
//   downstream `ExprNode` kinds.
//
// Status (A2 / v0.6): COMPILABLE skeleton. The `${...}` JS-escape block carries
//   the live surface; the .js shadow (translate-expr.js) runs (README
//   ANOMALY-2 ‚Äî the shadow discipline every native-parser file follows). No
//   live-pipeline wiring at A2 ‚Äî exercised by the per-kind translation unit
//   tests. Unit C1 wires it into the `nativeParseFile` FileAST assembler.

${
    // -----------------------------------------------------------------
    // translateExpr ‚Äî CALCULATION (pure). The module entry point.
    // Translate ONE native `Expr` node into ONE live `ExprNode`.
    //
    //   nativeExpr ‚Äî a native `Expr` (the `ast-expr.js` catalog).
    //
    // Returns ONE live `ExprNode`. Expressions are FLATTER than statements:
    // a native `Expr` always maps to exactly one live `ExprNode` ‚Äî the
    // "fan-out" in this bridge is kind-SELECTION (`IsCheck` -> one of four
    // binary ops), not node-count expansion. A missing / non-object input
    // folds to a zero-span `escape-hatch` so a caller never receives an
    // absence where an `ExprNode` is expected.
    //
    // (live surface in translate-expr.js ‚Äî the .scrml shape carries the
    // canonical Pillar 5b SHAPE; the .js shadow runs.)
    // -----------------------------------------------------------------
    export fn translateExpr(nativeExpr) {
        // see translate-expr.js for the running shadow
    }

    // -----------------------------------------------------------------
    // translateExprList ‚Äî CALCULATION (pure). Translate an array of native
    // `Expr` nodes into a live `ExprNode[]`. A missing / non-array input
    // folds to an empty array. Convenience for callers (C1) holding an
    // expression array.
    // -----------------------------------------------------------------
    export fn translateExprList(nativeExprs) {
        // see translate-expr.js for the running shadow
    }
}
